<emphasis box="[194,422,711,735]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="3134">Material examined.</emphasis>
Two males, Ile aux Fous, 
<quantity box="[774,850,710,734]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.78" pageId="12" pageNumber="3134" unit="m" value="17.8">17.8 m</quantity>
, 
<date box="[871,1106,710,734]" pageId="12" pageNumber="3134" value="2001-09-24">24 September 2001</date>
, 19‡39.023’S, 63‡22.934’E, under dead piece of plate coral over rubble.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[154,1111,710,894]" pageId="12" pageNumber="3134">
<emphasis box="[194,301,775,799]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="3134">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is easily recognized by the lack of rami on uropod 3 and by the elongate merus and short carpus of pereopods 3–4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[154,1111,710,894]" pageId="12" pageNumber="3134">
<emphasis box="[194,335,838,862]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="3134">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="LEDOYER, M." box="[726,905,838,862]" pageId="12" pageNumber="3134" pagination="197 - 332" refId="ref3193" refString="LEDOYER, M., 1978, Amphipodes gammariens (Crustacea) des biotopes cavitaires organogenes recifaux de l'ile Maurice (Ocean Indien), The Mauritius Institute Bulletin, 8 (3), 197 - 332." type="journal article" year="1978">Ledoyer (1978)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[990,1106,838,862]" name="Mauritius" pageId="12" pageNumber="3134">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
. The current record extends its known distribution within the Mascarene Islands.
</paragraph>
